MOONSHINE LILY was bumped at the break, raced well off the inside at the rear, was not a factor.

FIRE EXTINGUISHER dropped back a bit up the backstretch into the turn, went four to five wide on that bend, kept on in the stretch to get up for show honors. SERENDIP RULER had the early lead for the opening eighth of a mile, continued to press three wide, needed more in the stretch. ROMANCER exchanged a light brush at the start, shifted in, saved ground early on the turn, tipped out two to three wide late on that bend, ran on in the lane. VISION OF ELIAS stalked the leaders from outside, was within range four wide on the turn, lacked the needed late kick. STEPPIN SHEP veered in a bit at the gap, switched out and raced two to three wide on the turn, ran on. FROGGY veered in badly at the gap, raced inside on the turn. EL CHIHUAS chased from between rivals mid-pack, shifted in at the three-eighths, came up empty. TRADE DEADLINE chased from outside, went four to five wide on the turn and faded.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 9 6F Dirt CR: 50. Maiden Special Weight Purse 25200. FOR ACCREDITED OKLAHOMA-BREDS MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CATALE WINEMIXER switched off the inside early, settled off the pace, began to advance three then four wide on the turn, moved between runners past the quarter pole, drew clear. SURFER GIRL was forwardly-placed between runners, bid three wide, drifted in toward the rail in upper stretch, was no match for the winner but kept on and just saved the place in a head-bob. SPLITSECONDECISION moved forward inside up the backstretch, raced just off the leaders saving ground on the turn, altered outside a drifting rival three deep about the eighth pole, kicked on and just missed second. SULPHUR SUE was reluctant to load, stalked the pace from outside going five wide then forced out six wide late on the turn, kept on late to narrowly miss second and third. ALTERNATE ABBY raced off the pace going four wide on the turn, ran on evenly. NAUGHTY NOELLE was hard to load, broke awkwardly and slowly, brought up the rear into the turn and was forced five wide beginning that bend swinging seven deep into the stretch, showed mild late interest to improve position. HANNAH FO FANNAH was forwardly-placed racing four then five wide on the turn when forced out a bit past the quarter pole, weakened thereafter. GOSPEL EXPRESSION was in a bit tight on heels near the seven-sixteenths, switched out at that juncture and went three to five wide on the turn. OKIE HEAT raced mid-pack early near but off the inside, faded. GOLDIE'S LEGACY moved forward inside rivals racing just off the rail to take the lead, set a pressured pace, gave way. DUE TO TIMER MALFUNCTION RACE WAS HAND-TIMED.
